segments.text: Very briefly, I just want to say thank you to all of you for the privilege and opportunity to serve as Mayor Pro Tem for the next term.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_17

segments.text: I am honored that all of you, my new colleagues, have placed your trust in me to serve in this important leadership role for our city.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_17

segments.text: And I welcome the opportunity to expand my service to this council and the community we all love.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_17

segments.text: I am particularly humbled to be selected by the current composition of City Council, which as of this evening has become the most diverse in our city's history.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_17

segments.text: The magnitude of that honor and the responsibility that comes with it is not lost on me, nor is it lost on me that I will have the opportunity to serve as our city's first openly gay mayor pro tem in over two decades since Chris Colblast held this role.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_17

segments.text: I look forward to working with all of you and learning from each of you over the next two years to restore stability to this body, to maintain confidence in our government, to deliver exceptional city services, and to continue making progress towards our housing, transportation and climate goals.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_17

segments.text: and finally to advance the progressive policies that not only make Ann Arbor so great, such a great place to live, learn, work, raise a family, recreate and retire in, but also that set us apart as a model for the state and the nation.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_17

segments.text: So thank you and I look forward to serving with all of you.

segments.text: We now come to public comment.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: Public comment reserve time.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: Public comment reserve time is an opportunity for members of the public to speak to council about matters of municipal interest.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: Anyone may speak at public comment, but to do so, you must sign up in advance by contacting the city clerk on the day of the meeting.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: If you call before 1 o'clock, then your speaking time position will be allocated randomly within priority bands established by city council.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: If you call after one, then you will be placed at the end of the queue in the order of your call.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: If you contact the city clerk and attempt to sign up after 5 p.m., you will regrettably not have an opportunity to speak at city council.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: We have allocated 45 minutes to public comment at the beginning of the meeting, enough time for us to hear from at least 15 members of the public.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: If the 15th public commenter completes their comment prior to the end of that 45-minute period, then we will move on to the next person on our list.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: If that person is not present, or if they end their speaking time prior to the end of the 45-minute period, then we go on to the next person on our list, and so forth.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: If we come to the end of our 45-minute period and people remain on our list, then these persons will be moved to public comment overflow at the end of our meeting when we will resume the queue and receive public comment until the queue is completed.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: Either during initial public comment reserve time or public comment overflow, if you are not available to speak when your name is called, then you will lose your spot on the queue and will not have an opportunity to address counsel at the meeting.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: Only one person may speak at a time.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: Speakers are not authorized to delegate their cue slots to others.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: In all cases, speakers have three minutes in which to speak, so please pay close attention to the time.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: Our clerk or the time clock will notify you when 30 seconds are remaining and when your time is expired.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_02

segments.text: When your time is expired, please conclude your remarks and cede the floor.

segments.text: And my main concern is that we maybe we should table that because I think there's some major concerns.

segments.text: And the biggest issue that I have that should concern the city of Ann Arbor directly is the proposal that they put a paint shop in.

segments.text: Dear Ann Arbor City Council members, I'm calling tonight to urge you to turn down the proposed resolution regarding a lease between the city and Great Lakes Air Repair for a corporate hangar at the Ann Arbor Municipal Airport.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: My name is Terry Brown.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: I have been a very long-time user of this airport for more than 40 years as a pilot, flight instructor, and designated pilot examiner.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: I am very well acquainted with Mark Roizen and the Aviation Center, the current tenant of this corporate hangar.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: I, along with many of my customers, have relied upon Mr. Roizen for many years to repair, improve, and maintain many of the corporate and personal aircraft that I fly.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: I have purchased pilot supplies from his organization, rented aircraft, purchased fuel, and have both obtained and given flight instruction in his aircraft fleet.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: The current tenant brings a large volume of business to the airport as well as to the Ann Arbor community.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: If his lease is given to another operation and he is put out of business after 43 years at Ann Arbor, we will lose all of this business.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: He is a factory authorized service center for Cirrus Aircraft.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: He is a PSI testing center, giving many government written exams for not only pilots, but many other specialty fields as well.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: These franchises will very likely not be given to a new tenant.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: In all of the years that I've been a patron at this establishment, I've always been courteously treated in a professional manner and my needs have been met or exceeded.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: Competition in this space is extremely important.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: In order to ensure a fair pricing for all of the users of the airport, it is vitally necessary to have more than one supplier of these services.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: If the aviation center is no longer going to be operating at Ann Arbor, it needs to be replaced with another full-service FBO, providing maintenance, flight instruction, fuel sales, and aircraft rental at this field.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: Wouldn't our needs be better served by allowing this already proven business to continue serving this market as it has for so many years?
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: I urge you to not make a hasty decision, but to research the matter more thoroughly and to do what is best for all concerned.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: Thank you for your consideration.
segments.speaker: SPEAKER_15

segments.text: Thank you.
